Abstract: ''Gee, I guess we're the first,'' said Karen Minott, a Brooklyn resident who showed up at Grand Army Plaza about 5 p.m. with her cousin and a friend.    Ms. Minott cradled her sleeping 18-month-old daughter and looked about with that slightly embarrassed look people get when they suddenly realize they're early for a party. ''Where is everybody?'' she asked.
